Github for ninjas

Impress your friends with your Git skills.

Workflow


Install
-------
*Install git (for debian/debian based users)*

**$ sudo apt-get install git**

*Check if it's installed*

**$ git --version**


Upload
------
https://www.youtube.com/v/1zJzj-Lrrhw

*Initialize git*

**$ git init**

*Link your folder with the Github repository*

**$ git remote add origin REPOSITORY_LINK**

*Track*

**$ git add .**

*Commit*

**$ git commit -m "YOUR_MESSAGE"**

*Push*

**$ git push origin master**

**Write your Github username and password when asked**


Pull
----
https://www.youtube.com/v/3vK7T_kU3bY

*Initialize git*

**$ git init**

*Link your folder with the Github repository*

**$ git remote add origin REPOSITORY_LINK**

*Pull*

**$ git pull origin master**


Push
----
https://www.youtube.com/v/7ZAAYvy_ZbM

*Track*

**$ git add .**

*Commit*

**$ git commit -m "YOUR_MESSAGE"**

*Pull (in case another collaborator has made a commit)*

**$ git pull origin master**

*In case nano prompts*

**Press ctrl+X**

*Push*

**$ git push origin master**


Conflicts
---------

https://www.youtube.com/v/ByXRqhq6UfY

Don't be afraid of conflicts. Watch the video to learn how to to fix them.
